[start section id="20112"]

Reviewed outside colonoscopy report.
IMPRESSION
#1 Distal rectal mass
Mr. Morse is referred for further treatment of a distal rectal mass.  I discussed possible options with him both endoscopic and surgical, and given the nature of the lesion we would advise proceeding with a CT-scan and endoscopic ultrasound, after which patient will meet with Colon and Rectal Surgery for consideration of transanal excision, as given the distal location I believe endoscopic maneuvers will be difficult to remove the lesion and the size may be prohibitive.  I would request further biopsies to exclude malignancy.  MoviPrep prescription was provided to the patient, and I will meet with him again prior to the surgeon visit.   We requested slides.
#2 Vasovagal episode
Mr. Morse sustained a vasovagal episode while in our office.  He and his sister have both had these and they state this is their "normal" reaction during doctor visits.  He has had no problems with his colonoscopy or other previous physician visits other than an ophthalmology appointment.   After review with Dr. Rodriguez we will obtain ECG and send to cardiology for investigation.  I also reviewed Lynch syndrome with him.
Discussed with Dr. Jamie Rodriguez.  Note to follow.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

[end section id="20112"]

